verses.text_plain: And Joseph was brought down to Egypt; and Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him of the hands of the Ishmeelites, which had brought him down thither.
verses.verse_html: 1And Joseph was brought down to Egypt; and Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him of the hands of the Ishmeelites, which had brought him down thither.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord was with Joseph, and he was a prosperous man; and he was in the house of his master the Egyptian.
verses.verse_html: 2And the Lord was with Joseph, and he was a prosperous man; and he was in the house of his master the Egyptian.

verses.text_plain: And his master saw that the Lord was with him, and that the Lord made all that he did to prosper in his hand.
verses.verse_html: 3And his master saw that the Lord was with him, and that the Lord made all that he did to prosper in his hand.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph found grace in his sight, and he served him: and he made him overseer over his house, and all that he had he put into his hand.
verses.verse_html: 4And Joseph found grace in his sight, and he served him: and he made him overseer over his house, and all that he had he put into his hand.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass from the time that he had made him overseer in his house, and over all that he had, that the Lord blessed the Egyptian’s house for Joseph’s sake; and the blessing of the Lord was upon all that he had in the house, and in the field.
verses.verse_html: 5And it came to pass from the time that he had made him overseer in his house, and over all that he had, that the Lord blessed the Egyptian’s house for Joseph’s sake; and the blessing of the Lord was upon all that he had in the house, and in the field.

verses.text_plain: And he left all that he had in Joseph’s hand; and he knew not ought he had, save the bread which he did eat. And Joseph was a goodly person, and well favoured.
verses.verse_html: 6And he left all that he had in Joseph’s hand; and he knew not ought he had, save the bread which he did eat. And Joseph was a goodly person, and well favoured.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass after these things, that his master’s wife cast her eyes upon Joseph; and she said, Lie with me.
verses.verse_html: 7And it came to pass after these things, that his master’s wife cast her eyes upon Joseph; and she said, Lie with me.

verses.text_plain: But he refused, and said unto his master’s wife, Behold, my master wotteth not what is with me in the house, and he hath committed all that he hath to my hand;
verses.verse_html: 8But he refused, and said unto his master’s wife, Behold, my master wotteth not what is with me in the house, and he hath committed all that he hath to my hand;

verses.text_plain: There is none greater in this house than I; neither hath he kept back any thing from me but thee, because thou art his wife: how then can I do this great wickedness, and sin against God?
verses.verse_html: 9There is none greater in this house than I; neither hath he kept back any thing from me but thee, because thou art his wife: how then can I do this great wickedness, and sin against God?

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, as she spake to Joseph day by day, that he hearkened not unto her, to lie by her, or to be with her.

verses.text_plain: And Joseph’s master took him, and put him into the prison, a place where the king’s prisoners were bound: and he was there in the prison.
verses.verse_html: 20And Joseph’s master took him, and put him into the prison, a place where the king’s prisoners were bound: and he was there in the prison.

verses.text_plain: But the Lord was with Joseph, and shewed him mercy, and gave him favour in the sight of the keeper of the prison.

verses.text_plain: And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph’s hand all the prisoners that were in the prison; and whatsoever they did there, he was the doer of it.
verses.verse_html: 22And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph’s hand all the prisoners that were in the prison; and whatsoever they did there, he was the doer of it.

verses.text_plain: The keeper of the prison looked not to any thing that was under his hand; because the Lord was with him, and that which he did, the Lord made it to prosper.
verses.verse_html: 23The keeper of the prison looked not to any thing that was under his hand; because the Lord was with him, and that which he did, the Lord made it to prosper.
